SpyNet - a malware made with AutoIt

26 Dec 2014

I found this sample on malwr.com idly looking over scanns looking for interesting samples to reverse engineer. My main focus are for now looking at code written in c/c++ and when Protection ID showed c++ the sample got my interest.

Not soon enough I discovered it contained an AutoIt executable.

What is AutoIt?

AutoIt v3 is a freeware BASIC-like scripting language designed for automating the Windows GUI and general scripting. It uses a combination of simulated keystrokes, mouse movement and window/control manipulation in order to automate tasks in a way not possible or reliable with other languages (e.g. VBScript and SendKeys). AutoIt is also very small, self-contained and will run on all versions of Windows out-of-the-box with no annoying “runtimes” required!

Source: www.autoitscript.com

So for fast and rapid malware development AutoIt seems to be a good choice!

But the file came as .exe not .au3, it can be done with Aut2Exe, so the AutoIt runtime are embedded, similar to py2exe

Fortunately theres a simple extraction tool called exe2aut which produced this file.

It cointains lots of functions more or less skeletons for winapi calls in most cases. Though what interested me was the part in the end:
